# reorG Integration Conventions

## Adapter Pattern

All marketplace integrations implement a shared adapter interface:

```typescript
interface MarketplaceAdapter {
  fetchListings(cursor?: string): AsyncGenerator<RawListing[]>;
  fetchInventory(itemIds: string[]): Promise<InventoryMap>;
  pushPriceUpdate(updates: PriceUpdate[]): Promise<PushResult>;
  pushAdRateUpdate(updates: AdRateUpdate[]): Promise<PushResult>;
  // NO delete methods — ever
}
```

- Each adapter lives in `src/lib/integrations/` (ebay.ts, bigcommerce.ts, shopify.ts)
- Shared types in `src/lib/integrations/types.ts`
- Each adapter handles its own rate limiting, pagination, and error mapping

## Sync Rules

- Sync is always pull-only — it fetches data and updates `MarketplaceListing` records
- Sync NEVER writes to marketplaces
- Sync NEVER touches `StagedChange` records
- After fetching, the sync service runs SKU matching to link listings to `MasterRow`
- Unmatched listings go to `UnmatchedListing` table
- Every sync creates a `SyncJob` record with status, timing, item counts, and errors

## Push Rules

- Push goes through the write safety chain (lock checks → dry-run → confirmation → execute → audit)
- Push only modifies the specific fields the user confirmed (sale price, ad rate)
- Push creates a `PushJob` record with full payload and result
- Push triggers a targeted re-sync of affected listings after completion
- Auto-backup before bulk pushes (>10 items)

## Rate Limiting

- eBay: ~5000 calls/day; use bulk endpoints where available; 30-min sync interval
- BigCommerce: tier-based generous limits; 15-min sync interval
- Shopify: 2 req/sec REST or cost-based GraphQL; 15-min sync interval
- Implement exponential backoff on rate limit errors (429 responses)
- Log rate limit events to SyncJob errors

## Error Handling

- Map platform-specific errors to a unified error type
- Log raw API error payloads behind a technical detail toggle
- Surface plain-English summaries on the Errors page
- Send critical failure alerts via Resend email
